fix(import): request camera permission and lock scanner orientation

The QR scan button launched ZXing's CaptureActivity directly without
a CAMERA permission request, so on first use the activity rotated to
sensor-landscape and showed a frozen blank preview (camera init
failed with SecurityException, swallowed by the CameraManager).

- Declare android.permission.CAMERA in the app manifest (required=false
  so devices without a camera still install).
- Ask for CAMERA via ActivityResultContracts.RequestPermission before
  starting the scanner; only launch on grant.
- Pass setOrientationLocked(true) + explicit CaptureActivity so the
  scanner stays in whatever orientation the user had when pressing
  the button instead of forcing sensor-landscape.
